import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='X', y='Y', hue='Series')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What is the correlation between X and Y for each series?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    # Calculate mean and standard deviation for each series
    summary_stats = data.groupby('Series').agg({'X': ['mean', 'std'], 'Y': ['mean', 'std']}).reset_index()
    
    # Melt the summary_stats dataframe for easier plotting
    summary_stats_melted = summary_stats.melt(id_vars='Series', var_name=['Variable', 'Statistic'])
    
    # Create the bar chart
    chart = sns.barplot(x='Series', y='value', hue='Statistic', data=summary_stats_melted)
    
    # Rotate x-axis labels if necessary
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45)
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the mean and standard deviation of X and Y for each series?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data, x="X", hue="Series", multiple="stack", alpha=0.7)
    sns.histplot(data, x="Y", hue="Series", multiple="stack", alpha=0.7)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of X and Y for each series?", wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
